        FAQ
      </div>
      <div class = "container-fluid">
      <div class="content center-block">
        <div class = "row row-centered">
        <div class = "col-md-6 col-centered">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
           Who is eligible for Out of the Box?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            Any full-time high school student and U.S. resident attending a public, private, or home-school in the Greater Boston Area at the time of his/her application, where the Greater Boston Area is defined as schools/homes within a 30-mile radius of Boston City Hall (1 City Hall Square, Boston, MA 02201).  All students who meet the eligibility requirements will be considered, but we especially encourage students to apply that satisfy the following criteria:
            <br /> <br />
            <ul>
              <li>Have little/zero experience participating in National Science Competitions/ Fairs/Olympiads or writing technical proposals</li>
              <li>Coming from a high school with low admittance rates to top-tier colleges, especially rural or predominantly minority high schools</li>
              <li>Potentially the first family member to attend college</li>
              <li>Absence of science and engineering degrees in family</li>
              <li>Underserved, defined as coming from low socioeconomic means, which may be indicated by qualification for free/reduced lunch</li>
              </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
       <div class = "col-md-6 col-centered">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            What should my proposal look like?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            The Out of the Box competition is, at its core, about a cool idea or project that a student or group of students wants to develop; we encourage applicants to submit proposals in whatever form they feel best conveys their idea. The proposal should focus on summarizing your ideaâ€™s feasibility, impact, and innovation. Some examples of potential proposals are listed below, but feel free to utilize a method not listed.
            <br /> <br />
            <ul>
              <li> Written paper (1-2 pages total) </li>
              <li> Video (under 5 min length) submission </li>
            </ul>
            <br />

          </div>
        </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class = "row">
      <div class = "col-md-6 col-centered">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            How do I apply to the program?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
             Applications are closed for this year, and will open again early next fall!
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class = "col-md-6 col-centered">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            How are the proposals evaluated?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            Proposals are evaluated by their feasibility, impact, and innovation, as well as the passion demonstrated by the student in their writing as well as in the answers to the additional short-answer questions.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class = "row">
      <div class = "col-md-6">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            How does the program work, once the finalists are accepted?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            Once the finalists are accepted, they will work with mentors on the THINK team as well as MIT professors in the associated field to develop their project proposal further and learn more about the surrounding field of science.  After this process, the finalists that have demonstrated sufficient passion and dedication will selected as winners and be given $1,000 in seed funding to develop their projects to reality in the future, as well as $1,000 in an educational scholarship.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class = "col-md-6">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            How much does the program cost?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            Out of the Box is completely free of charge, and we will also take care of any travel expenses and equipment costs.  Everything's on us!
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class = "row">
      <div class = "col-md-6">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            How many students are accepted as finalists?  How many of these will be selected as winners?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            There is no set number, but we expect to choose up to 15 students as finalists, and as many deserving finalists as possible as winners.  
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class = "col-md-6">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="question">
            What if I'm not accepted as a finalist? Does Out of the Box have a place for me?
          </div>
           <br />
          <div class="answer">
            Yes, definitely!  For every applicant that applies, we will be hosting a preview weekend with lab tours, workshops about how to pursue research and science in general, as well as other fun activities.  Look out for more details about this weekend coming soon!  
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
